*dcopperl-3.4.0-r1 (19 Mar 2005)

  19 Mar 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> +dcopperl-3.4.0-r1.ebuild:
  Don't clobber perllocal.pod; use the functions from perl-module.eclass to
  handle it properly. Fixes bug 83520. Credit goes to Yaakov S, who also
  submitted the change to perl-module.eclass.

  18 Mar 2005; Daniel Goller <morfic@gentoo.org> dcopperl-3.4.0.ebuild:
  Added to ~ppc

  13 Mar 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> dcopperl-3.4.0.ebuild:
  KDE 3.4.0 ebuilds. Note that the tarballs won't be officially released for a
  few more days.

*dcopperl-3.4.0_rc1 (27 Feb 2005)

  27 Feb 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> +dcopperl-3.4.0_rc1.ebuild:
  Ebuild for 3.4.0 RC1.

*dcopperl-3.4.0_beta2-r1 (19 Feb 2005)

  19 Feb 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> +dcopperl-3.3.1-r2.ebuild,
  +dcopperl-3.4.0_beta2-r1.ebuild:
  Moved all versions to SLOT 0, because they install in /usr, and the
  different SLOTs were overwriting one another. Bug 80858.

  11 Feb 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> dcopperl-3.3.1-r1.ebuild:
  Added x86 (stable) keyword.

*dcopperl-3.3.1-r1 (05 Feb 2005)

  05 Feb 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org>
  +files/installdirs-vendor.diff, +dcopperl-3.3.1-r1.ebuild,
  dcopperl-3.4.0_beta2.ebuild:
  Install the perl modules under vendor_perl, not site_perl. Fixes bug 42819.

*dcopperl-3.4.0_beta2 (05 Feb 2005)

  05 Feb 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> +dcopperl-3.4.0_beta2.ebuild:
  Ebuild for 3.4.0_beta2. Note that beta2 has NOT been released as of this
  date. This ebuild is for inside testing by the KDE team, and is of course
  package.masked.

  10 Dec 2004; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> files/no-gtk-glib-check.diff,
  dcopperl-3.3.1.ebuild:
  Fixed compile failure when gtk is not installed.

  25 Nov 2004; Sven Wegener <swegener@gentoo.org> :
  Added missing digest entries.

*dcopperl-3.3.1 (06 Nov 2004)

  06 Nov 2004; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org>
  +files/no-gtk-glib-check.diff, +dcopperl-3.3.1.ebuild:
  Initial version of the split-up kdebindings ebuilds. Cf.
  kde-metaebuilds.berlios.de. This is a project to split the monolithic kde
  ebuilds into separate ebuilds for separate applications. These ebuilds are
  packaged.masked at first, pending testing.

